.TH "get_vm_area" 9 "get_vm_area" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_vm_area \- reserve a contiguous kernel virtual area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct vm_struct *" get_vm_area
.BI "(unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
size of the area
.IP "flags" 12
VM_IOREMAP for I/O mappings or VM_ALLOC
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Search an area of \fIsize\fP in the kernel virtual mapping area,
and reserved it for out purposes.  Returns the area descriptor
on success or NULL on failure.
.SH "RETURN"
the area descriptor on success or NULL on failure.
